programme.title: Live MNF
programme.desc: Everton v Swansea City (Kick-off 8.00pm). Coverage of the top-flight clash at Goodison Park, where the Toffees welcome another side struggling at the wrong end of the Premier League table. Everton have endured a difficult season so far, with Ronald Koeman losing his job and a poor run of form under David Unsworth following, but they managed to defeat West Ham United 4-0 in his final match in charge, and new permanent boss Sam Allardyce will be looking to build on that. Meanwhile, the Swans will have been hoping for a continuation of the resurgent form that saw them pull away from the relegation zone towards the back end of last season, but such form has failed to materialise, and a repeat of those inspired performances appears likely to be required in the latter stages of this campaign(n)
